http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/DGP-reviews-IFR-preparations/article13995575.ece

Director-General of Police, Andhra Pradesh, J.V. Ramudu, said that over 15,000 police force, along with National Security Guards (NSG), Special Protection Group (SPG), and paramilitary forces drawn from various units such as the CRFP, the BSF, and the ITBP, will be put on duty for the upcoming International Fleet Review (IFR) to be held in Visakhapatnam from February 4 to 9. Reviewing the security preparedness here on Monday, the DGP pointed out that, if required, additional forces and equipment such as DFM, HHMD, and other communication equipment, will be requisitioned from Telangana.IFR is a very important event in which about 50 countries will be participating with their naval fleet. Apart from a host of Central and State Ministers, VVIPs and international delegates, IFR witness the participation of President Pranab Mukherjee, Prime Minister Narendra Modi, and Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu. The DGP also reviewed the crowd and traffic management plans.